{"questionId":"19757","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A factory produces engraved gold disks. The cost <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> of the disks is directly proportional to the&nbsp;cube of the radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> of the disk.</p>\n<p>A disk with a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo></math>cm costs <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo> </mo></math>US dollars (USD).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find, to the nearest USD, the cost of disk that has a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo></math>cm.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>732</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>$</mo><mn>975</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>974</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>853</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>974</mn></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>732</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math> .</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19757","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.2b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find, to the nearest USD, the cost of disk that has a radius of 1.1 cm.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}